-- Beijing Enterprises Water to Buy Sewage Assets for $44 Million
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2013-07-02T02:29:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-02/beijing-enterprises-water-to-buy-sewage-assets-for-44-million.html
Beijing Enterprises Water Group Ltd. (371) ,
a developer of water-treatment systems, said unit BEWG
Environmental Group Co. agreed to buy a 60 percent stake in a
sewage-plant owner for 270 million  yuan  ($44 million).  Target BCEG Environment Development Co. has 26 sewage
treatment plants with a total design capacity of 937,500 tons
per day, Beijing Enterprises said today in a statement to the
Hong Kong stock exchange.  The move will “promote the group’s investment and
development in the Yangtze River Delta economic region” and
“strengthen the group’s regional influence in Beijing City,”
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Feifei Shen in Beijing at 
